        <div class="chapter" data-narrate="true">
            <div class="chapter-title">üåø CHAPTER ONE: The Inspiration</div>
            
            <p>Now gather 'round, friends, and let me tell you about the time Brer Sheep got into the wellness industry. And by "wellness industry," I mean selling questionable supplements out of his barn to anyone gullible enough to believe that dried grass clippings could cure arthritis.</p>

            <p>It all started when Brer Sheep was watching late-night TV and saw one of them infomercials for miracle pills that promised to make you younger, smarter, stronger, and more attractive ‚Äì basically everything you ain't.</p>

            <div class="dialogue">
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span> (watching TV at 3 AM): "This is BRILLIANT! They're selling hope in a bottle!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">TV Announcer</span>: "Made from ancient Tibetan herbs harvested by monks under the full moon!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "I got herbs! I got a full moon! I don't got monks, but I got... uh... enthusiasm!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Rabbit</span> (walking past): "Why are you up at 3 AM watching supplement commercials?"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "Research! Market research! Brer Rabbit, we're opening a pharmacy!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Rabbit</span>: "You ain't got no pharmaceutical license."<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span> (waving hand dismissively): "Details! We'll call it 'herbal supplements' ‚Äì that way we don't need FDA approval!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Rabbit</span>: "That sounds illegal."<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "Illegal is such a strong word. I prefer 'creatively compliant.'"
            </div>

            <p>The next morning, Brer Sheep was up at dawn, converting his barn into what he called "The Wellness Barn" ‚Äì a holistic healing center that was about as holistic as a gas station hot dog.</p>
        </div>

