        <div class="chapter" data-narrate="true">
            <div class="chapter-title">üé™ CHAPTER TWO: The Marketing Genius</div>

            <p>Brer Sheep knew that the secret to selling snake oil wasn't the product ‚Äì it was the marketing. So he hired Brer Raccoon, who had experience in "creative advertising" (he'd been run out of three counties for false advertising, but Brer Sheep saw that as qualifications).</p>

            <div class="dialogue">
                <span class="character">Brer Raccoon</span>: "What we need are TESTIMONIALS! Real people saying real things about your products!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "But nobody's tried them yet."<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Raccoon</span>: "So? We make 'em up! Nobody checks this stuff!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "Isn't that fraud?"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Raccoon</span>: "Only if you get caught."
            </div>

            <p>They put up signs all over Briar County with quotes from totally real people who definitely existed:</p>

            <div class="testimonial">
                "I took WOOL POWER‚Ñ¢ for one week and now I can lift a car! My wife left me because I'm too strong now!"<br>
                <div class="testimonial-author">- Definitely Real Jim, Age 45, Real Place, USA</div>
            </div>

            <div class="testimonial">
                "BRAIN FLEECE‚Ñ¢ made me so smart I solved world hunger! But I forgot to write it down. Taking more BRAIN FLEECE‚Ñ¢ to remember!"<br>
                <div class="testimonial-author">- Actual Person Sarah, Legitimate Town, Real State</div>
            </div>

            <div class="testimonial">
                "The ETERNAL YOUTH ELIXIR‚Ñ¢ took 50 years off my life! I'm now younger than my children! They're very confused!"<br>
                <div class="testimonial-author">- Probably Exists Margaret, Some Place Somewhere</div>
            </div>

            <p>The marketing worked. Within days, animals from all over were lining up at The Wellness Barn, desperate to buy miracle cures for problems they didn't even have.</p>

            <div class="action">*Brer Sheep counts money while wearing a white coat he bought at a thrift store*</div>
        </div>

        <div class="chapter" data-narrate="true">
            <div class="chapter-title">ü§ë CHAPTER THREE: Business is Booming</div>

            <p>The Wellness Barn became the hottest spot in Briar County. Brer Sheep couldn't bottle his questionable concoctions fast enough. He had Brer Fox mixing potions in the back, Brer Possum labeling bottles (mostly upside down, but nobody noticed), and Brer Turtle doing quality control (he fell asleep, so there wasn't any).</p>

            <div class="dialogue">
                <span class="character">Brer Bear</span> (at the counter): "I'll take three bottles of WOOL POWER‚Ñ¢! I wanna get STRONG!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "Excellent choice! That'll be $149.97!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Bear</span>: "When will I see results?"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "Oh, immediately! Or eventually. Or possibly never. Results may vary based on, you know, reality."<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Bear</span>: "What?"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span> (quickly): "I SAID IT WORKS GREAT BYE THANK YOU FOR YOUR MONEY!"
            </div>

            <p>Brer Wolf came in with back pain. Brer Sheep sold him DETOX DELUXE‚Ñ¢. When Brer Wolf pointed out that detox doesn't treat back pain, Brer Sheep explained that the back pain was probably caused by "toxins" and therefore detox was the answer. Brer Wolf bought six bottles.</p>

            <p>Brer Crow flew in complaining about not being able to sleep. Brer Sheep sold him BRAIN FLEECE‚Ñ¢ (which was loaded with caffeine). When Brer Crow came back three days later looking like he hadn't slept in a week, Brer Sheep sold him MORE BRAIN FLEECE‚Ñ¢, explaining that he just needed a "higher dose."</p>

            <div class="action">*Cha-ching! Cha-ching! Cha-ching!*</div>

            <p>Money was rolling in faster than Brer Sheep could count it. He bought himself a new tractor, a fancy hat, and seventeen gaming consoles (he learned nothing from the tax evasion incident).</p>
        </div>

        <div class="chapter" data-narrate="true">
            <div class="chapter-title">‚ö†Ô∏è CHAPTER FOUR: The Side Effects</div>

            <p>About two weeks into the business, things started going sideways. Turns out when you sell people bottles of random stuff mixed in your barn, sometimes there are... consequences.</p>

            <p>Brer Bear, who'd been taking WOOL POWER‚Ñ¢ religiously, showed up at the barn looking distressed.</p>

            <div class="dialogue">
                <span class="character">Brer Bear</span>: "Brer Sheep! Something's wrong!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "What is it?"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Bear</span>: "I'm growing WOOL! Look!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span> (staring): "...that's just fur."<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Bear</span>: "NO! It's WOOL! Your product turned me into a sheep-bear hybrid!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "Brer Bear, you're a bear. You have fur. You've always had fur."<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Bear</span>: "But it's FLUFFIER now! That's not normal!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "That's called... winter coat. It happens every year."<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Bear</span>: "...oh."
            </div>

            <p>Then Brer Crow came in, and he was a different story entirely.</p>

            <div class="dialogue">
                <span class="character">Brer Crow</span> (vibrating): "I-CAN'T-STOP-TALKING-AND-I-HAVEN'T-SLEPT-IN-FOUR-DAYS-AND-I-CAN-SEE-SOUNDS-AND-HEAR-COLORS-AND‚Äî"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "Ah. Yeah. That's the caffeine. You might wanna cut back on the BRAIN FLEECE‚Ñ¢."<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Crow</span>: "CUT-BACK?!-I-JUST-BOUGHT-TEN-MORE-BOTTLES-BECAUSE-I-THOUGHT-I-NEEDED-MORE!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "Oh no."<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Crow</span>: "ALSO-I-THINK-I-CAN-FLY-FASTER-THAN-LIGHT-WANNA-SEE?!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "Please don't try that."
            </div>

            <p>But the worst was Brer Possum. He'd been "testing" the ETERNAL YOUTH ELIXIR‚Ñ¢ (which was mostly apple cider vinegar and glitter) and was now convinced he was Benjamin Button.</p>

            <div class="dialogue">
                <span class="character">Brer Possum</span> (sobbing): "I'm aging BACKWARDS! Yesterday I was 40, today I'm 35, tomorrow I'll be 30! Eventually I'll be a BABY!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Rabbit</span>: "Brer Possum, you look exactly the same."<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Possum</span>: "That's what someone who doesn't understand SCIENCE would say!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Rabbit</span>: "It's GLITTER and VINEGAR!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Possum</span>: "I'm gonna need diapers soon! DIAPERS!"
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="warning-box">
            <h3>‚ö†Ô∏è REALITY CHECK ‚ö†Ô∏è</h3>
            <p>At this point in the story, several customers were experiencing:</p>
            <ul style="text-align: left; color: #f0e6d2; margin: 15px 0; padding-left: 40px;">
                <li>Extreme caffeine addiction (Brer Crow)</li>
