                <li>Intestinal distress (everyone who took DETOX DELUXE‚Ñ¢)</li>
                <li>Empty wallets (everyone)</li>
                <li>Regret (also everyone)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="chapter" data-narrate="true">
            <div class="chapter-title">üö® CHAPTER FIVE: The Authorities</div>

            <p>Word of The Wellness Barn's "miracle cures" eventually reached the wrong ears ‚Äì specifically, the ears of Health Inspector Badger, who was ALSO a cousin of IRS Agent Badger. (The Badgers were a very law-enforcement-oriented family.)</p>

            <p>Inspector Badger showed up at The Wellness Barn with a clipboard, a serious expression, and a profound lack of patience for Brer Sheep's nonsense.</p>

            <div class="dialogue">
                <span class="character">Inspector Badger</span>: "I'm here to inspect this... 'wellness center.'"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span> (nervously): "Everything's above board! All natural! Completely legitimate!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Inspector Badger</span> (picking up a bottle): "What's in this?"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "Herbs!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Inspector Badger</span> (reading label): "It says 'proprietary blend.'"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "Proprietary herbs!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Inspector Badger</span>: "This is grass clippings."<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "Artisanal grass clippings."
            </div>

            <p>Inspector Badger went through the entire barn, finding violations at every turn. Unsanitary mixing conditions. Unlabeled ingredients. False advertising. Products that claimed to cure diseases without any scientific backing whatsoever. And in the back room, he found Brer Fox literally mixing potions in a bucket with a stick.</p>

            <div class="dialogue">
                <span class="character">Inspector Badger</span>: "Is that... is that a bucket?"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Fox</span>: "It's a PHARMACEUTICAL VESSEL."<br><br>
                <span class="character">Inspector Badger</span>: "It's a BUCKET. From Home Depot. I can still see the price tag."<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Fox</span>: "...I can explain."<br><br>
                <span class="character">Inspector Badger</span>: "Don't."
            </div>

            <p>Inspector Badger shut down The Wellness Barn on the spot. Posted a giant "CLOSED BY HEALTH DEPARTMENT" sign on the door. Confiscated all the products. And gave Brer Sheep a citation so long it looked like a CVS receipt.</p>

            <div class="action">*Brer Sheep watches his empire crumble in real-time*</div>
        </div>

        <div class="chapter" data-narrate="true">
            <div class="chapter-title">üí∏ CHAPTER SIX: The Refunds</div>

            <p>The worst part wasn't the shut-down. The worst part was that Brer Sheep had to give REFUNDS.</p>

            <p>Every single customer who'd bought his questionable supplements came back demanding their money. And since Brer Sheep had already spent most of it on gaming consoles and a fancy hat, he had to get creative.</p>

            <div class="dialogue">
                <span class="character">Brer Bear</span>: "I want my $149.97 back!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "But... didn't you feel stronger?"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Bear</span>: "NO! I felt FLUFFIER! That's not the same thing!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span> (handing over money): "Here's your refund."<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Bear</span>: "...is this Monopoly money?"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "It's... transitional currency."<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Bear</span>: "I WANT REAL MONEY!"
            </div>

            <p>Brer Sheep had to sell his fancy hat, return the gaming consoles, and even sell his tractor (again ‚Äì this was becoming a pattern) just to cover all the refunds. By the end of it, he was broker than he'd been before he started the whole operation.</p>

            <p>But wait ‚Äì there was MORE trouble!</p>

            <p>Turns out, selling supplements without FDA approval was a federal offense. And who showed up to deal with federal offenses? That's right ‚Äì Agent Badger from the IRS, who was VERY pleased to see Brer Sheep again.</p>

            <div class="dialogue">
                <span class="character">Agent Badger</span>: "Twice in one year, Mr. Sheep? I'm impressed."<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "This is different! This was SUPPLEMENTS!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Agent Badger</span>: "This was FRAUD."<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "...can I go back to the briar patch?"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Agent Badger</span>: "Absolutely not."
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="chapter" data-narrate="true">
            <div class="chapter-title">‚öñÔ∏è CHAPTER SEVEN: The Settlement</div>

            <p>After some negotiation (and Brer Sheep agreeing to NEVER sell supplements again), they reached a settlement:</p>

            <ul style="color: #f0e6d2; margin: 20px 0; padding-left: 40px;">
                <li>Brer Sheep would pay a fine of $10,000</li>
                <li>Attend a course on "Legal vs. Illegal Business Practices"</li>
                <li>Perform 200 hours of community service at the actual pharmacy in town</li>
                <li>Publicly apologize to everyone he scammed</li>
                <li>Stop watching infomercials at 3 AM</li>
            </ul>

            <p>The public apology was the worst part.</p>

            <div class="dialogue">
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span> (standing in town square): "I, Brer Sheep, would like to apologize for selling you all fake miracle cures that were actually just grass, vinegar, and false hope."<br><br>
                <span class="character">Crowd</span>: "BOO!"<br><br>
